8 Section 3. Section 52-3-812, MCA, is amended to read:
9 "52-3-812. Content of report. (1) The report required by 52-3-811 may be made in writing or orally,
10 by telephone, in person, or electronically through the department. A person who receives an oral report shall
11 prepare it in writing as soon as possible.
12 (2) The report referred to under this section must contain:
13 (a) the names and addresses of the vulnerable adult and the person, if any, responsible for the
14 vulnerable adult's care;
15 (b) the name and address, if available, of the person who is alleged to have abused, sexually
16 abused, neglected, or exploited the vulnerable adult;
17 (c) to the extent known, the vulnerable adult's age and the nature and extent of the abuse, sexual
18 abuse, neglect, or exploitation, including any evidence of previous injuries, abuse, sexual abuse, neglect, or
19 exploitation sustained by the vulnerable adult and any evidence of prior instances of abuse, sexual abuse,
20 neglect, or exploitation of other vulnerable adults committed by the person alleged to have committed abuse,
21 sexual abuse, neglect, or exploitation; and
22 (d) the name, telephone number, and address of the person making the report."
23
24 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 and 2] are intended to be codified
25 as an integral part of Title 52, chapter 3, part 8, and the provisions of Title 52, chapter 3, part 8, apply to
26 [sections 1 and 2].
